    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVE -
        CYLINDER SLEEVE INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CYLINDER SLEEVE INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Be sure the O-Rings are properly aligned in the groove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the lower crankcase counterbore, then install the sleeve carefully. If reusing
                sleeve, rotate 90&#176; from original position and install in the same bore from which it was removed.
                Press sleeve into place by hand applying pressure evenly on each side (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150657">6.57</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150655" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11601" filename="../figcg1/cg11601.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.55. Assemble Connecting Rod and Piston.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150656" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12130" filename="../figcg1/cg12130.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.56. Install Cylinder Sleeve O-Rings.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150657" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12131" filename="../figcg1/cg12131.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.57. Install Cylinder Sleeve.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
